title: For Sale:  Missouri Concealed Carry Class - Texas County area
postcontent:
I am offering an opportunity for folks in the Texas County area to attend a Concealed Carry course needed to obtain your Missouri Concealed Carry permit. Before you ask, yes, I am on the Texas County approved instructor list, so no worries there.

I am an instructor with Canovi and Associates in the Springfield area and will be in the Houston, Mo. area over Christmas and New Year's weekends. Christmas weekend I can either work a course in a 2-day format or a 1-day format, New Year's will be a 1- day format. Mr. Canovi has given the go-ahead to hold a class on those date-frames, but they will not be on the Canovi schedule if you check their webpage.

The class meets the standards required by Missouri Statute and is an 8 hour course. You will need NO less than 70 rounds (25 familiarization for revolver, 25 familiarization for semiautomatic, and 20 to qualify). Rentals will not be available for these dates, so if you need a revolver or semiauto please borrow one or buddy up with someone prior to.

Reserve quickly so I can guarantee that we will have a facility, which has already been approved, I just need to confirm if a class is going to be held for the owners. Do not worry if you cannot attend either of those time frames, you can always come to the Springfield area and take a course or ask when I can be in the area again for a course...groups make it easier to teach a course, but if I'm already in the area and get just 1 student I will still teach the course.

Reservations require:
Full Name
Mailing Address
Contact Phone Number
Preference of 1 or 2 day course and what dates would work best on Christmas or New Year's (Thurs-Sat on either)
Do you own a semiautomatic AND a revoler? If not, can you obtain both for class?

Payment: Payment will be taken day-of, please bring exact change as I will not be able to provide change that day.

Canovi's Books and DVD's: If you are interested in purchasing Matt Canovi's REAL Defensive System book or the DVD's, please express that with your course reservation so I can obtain the needed copies for you to purchase that day.

**Concealed Carry Plus - This course is designed to provide folks who carry some advanced skills beyond the very basics that are needed to survive a gunfight. You'll learn front sight shooting, point shooting, multiple shots for stopping power, low light techniques, and single hand shooting techniques. This portion adds approximately 1 hour to the 8 hour course and will require 20-30 rounds of ammo. If you already have a CCW class and want to take the Plus portion, please contact me as well. I can work those individuals in. Just know that the $15 difference ONLY applies to those attending both classes.

Fees:
$75 for the Missouri Concealed Carry course (certificate provided at the end of the course)
$90 for the Missouri Concealed Carry course and the CC Plus.
$24 for just the Plus portion

title: For Sale:  Savage 111  7mm  Rem.  Mag
location: Wake Forest/Youngsville, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
This Savage  model 111 7mm Rem. Mag is still very new. Only fired 9  times.

  A  couple  things  to  note  about  this  rifle.  First; this  model  does  not  have  the  accu-trigger. Second; the  scope  included  is  the  original  “stock”  scope,  and isn't very good. This  rifle  is  certainly  worthy  of  a  good  scope  and  you'll  want  to  invest  in  one  if  you  plan  on  doing  any  long  range  shooting.

Concerning  the  trigger  heres  something  I  think  people  should  know,  and  I  speak  with  experience  as  a  former  Marine  who  has  had  much  formal  marksmanship  training  when  I  say  this....while  it's  true  that  this  stock  111  trigger  is  not  the  greatest  thing  savage  ever  designed,  I  can  tell  you  that  as  long  as  you  understand  and  are  employing  the  basic  principles  of  marksmanship  such  as  a  slow  steady  trigger  squeeze,  breath  control,  and  aren't  anticipating  the  shot,  this  is  still  a  very  accurate  rifle  even  with  the  stock  trigger. Right  out  of  the  box  and  with  the freebie scope I  shot  1”  groups  at  100  yards  effortlessly.  You  also  should  know  that  for  much  less  than  the  difference  in  cost  of  an  accu-trigger  model  you  can  purchase  a  “rifle  basix”  trigger  for  the  savage  111  (around  $89)  which  is  widely  considered  to  be  even  better  than  the  accu-trigger  if  you  want  to  do  some  serious  500  yard+  shooting.

Still in Box...price tag says $399.99. You're  also  saving all the  sales  tax, (approx. $25)  getting  a  butt-stock  cartridge  sleeve  ($10),  and  20  rounds  of  150gr  soft  points ($24.97).

$340 is the bottom line price and it's FIRM. I will not respond to offers for less. I'm already in the hole at this price. I've had 3 offers for less, and right here it still sits...not in a hurry. Besides, it's freakin awesome to shoot and ridiculously powerful so I don't mind keeping it awhile longer!

Serious Inquiries please call Steve at  REDACTED instead of playing e-mail tag. PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE! I am a full time student and cannot always answer my phone. I check my messages after each class and will get back to you asap.

title: For Sale:  Century M70 AK-47 7.62 X 39
postcontent:
This is a Century International Arms M70 Fixed Stock AK-47 (M70B1) in very near mint condition. 99% of the M70s out there are under-folders and the fixed stock version is hard to find as very few of these were made. The metal is excellent and the wood is very nice. This AK has grenade launching capability and grenade launching sight as shown in the pictures.

The rifle shoots the popular 7.62x39 caliber. It is very accurate, features a threaded muzzle with a slant brake installed Two mil-surp metal 30 round mag's and Green canvas sling,bayonet lug,bayonet and scabbard (number matching) and heavy duty bipod with 200 rounds of Ammo,upgraded Black fore end with UltiMAK M9 optic mount ( Wood Fore end Included ).Barrel: 16 1/4", Overall: 34 1/4".

The rifle is a combination of original Yugoslavian rifle parts and U.S.-made compliance parts. The fit and finish of the rifle is more than acceptable, with an evenly applied Parkerized finish and an above-average-condition wood fore-end.

The M70B1 has some novel features that set it apart from the run-of-the-mill AK variant. First, it has the enlarged and reinforced area around the trunnion like the RPK on its stamped receiver. In addition, a unique grenade ladder sight located on the gas block, when rotated into its upward open position, provides meter range marks and cuts off the gas port in the gas block. Also, the rifle features front and rear flip-up night sights, although the luminous material has long since disappeared. Has a smooth and comfortable trigger.
